<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="fr">
  <head>
    <title><%= content_for(:title) || "Vera Trade — Le magazine des voitures qui ont une âme" %></title>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1,viewport-fit=cover">
    <meta name="description" content="<%= content_for(:description) || "Vera Trade — La marketplace éditoriale des youngtimers, voitures de collection et préparations. Chaque annonce, une histoire. Chaque châssis, un Rust Map." %>">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-status-bar-style" content="black-translucent">
    <meta name="apple-mobile-web-app-title" content="Vera Trade">
    <meta name="mobile-web-app-capable" content="yes">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0A0A0A">
    <meta name="application-name" content="Vera Trade">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= csp_meta_tag %>

    <%= yield :head %>

    <!-- PWA Manifest -->
    <link rel="manifest" href="/manifest.webmanifest">

    <!-- Icons -->
    <link rel="icon" href="/icon.png" type="image/png">
    <link rel="icon" href="/icon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/icons/apple-touch-icon.png">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="152x152" href="/icons/icon-152x152.png">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="/icons/icon-180x180.png">

    <!-- Fonts: préconnexion CDN Google (TODO: self-host RGPD en PR dédiée) -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>

    <%= stylesheet_link_tag :app, "data-turbo-track": "reload" %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag "application", "data-turbo-track": "reload", type: "module", nonce: true %>
  </head>

  <body class="min-h-screen bg-bg-primary text-text-primary font-body antialiased">
    <%= render "shared/top_nav" %>

    <% if notice %>
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 mt-6">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent-red bg-bg-secondary px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-text-primary"><%= notice %></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
    <% if alert %>
      <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 mt-6">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-accent-red-dark bg-bg-secondary px-5 py-4">
          <p class="font-body text-sm text-accent-red"><%= alert %></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <main class="pt-[72px] lg:pt-[80px]">
      <%= yield %>
    </main>

    <%= render "shared/footer" %>

    <%= render "shared/bottom_nav" if user_signed_in? %>

    <%#
      Service Worker registration is intentionally DISABLED right now.

      Why: veratrade.fr previously served FlowMotor, which registered a
      cache-first PWA worker at scope "/". That ghost worker still lives
      in early visitors' browsers and intercepts our pages. Re-running
      `navigator.serviceWorker.register(...)` here would immediately
      re-install the current kamikaze worker (app/views/pwa/service-worker.js)
      which unregisters itself on activate — creating an install/kamikaze
      loop on every navigation.

      Strategy (D1 / fix/sw-kamikaze): rely on browsers' built-in 24h SW
      update check. The browser will fetch /service-worker.js, install the
      kamikaze, let it wipe caches + unregister, and then stay SW-free.
      No `register(...)` call from our side is needed for the cleanup.

      TO RE-ENABLE PWA LATER: restore the `navigator.serviceWorker.register`
      block below AND replace the kamikaze body with a real worker. See
      app/views/pwa/service-worker.js for the full rollback instructions.
    %>
  </body>
</html>
